AN INVESTIGATION into allegations that Cape Town mayor Patricia de Lille had been involved in leaking confidential DA documents to the media has been abandoned.In February, it was alleged that De Lille had been involved in the leakage of documents to an Afrikaans Sunday newspaper.DA federal council chairperson James Selfe referred the matter to the party s Federal Legal Commission for investigation and also to determine the role played by De Lille and DA chief whip in the Cape Town metro Shaun August.However, it has emerged that the investigation had to be curtailed when the writer of the report refused to disclose his sources.DENNIS CRUYWAGEN news@thenewage.co.za